Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: NUMA Support Module

Provides advanced NUMA (Non-Uniform Memory Access) support for memory allocation and management.

Features:
- NUMA node detection and topology discovery
- Memory binding and interleaving
- Memory migration between nodes
- NUMA-aware allocation and GC integration
- AI/agent-friendly NUMA APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: NUMA Support Types and Interfaces
Type called "NUMASupport":
    detect_nodes as Function that takes no arguments returns List[NUMANode]
    bind_memory as Function that takes pointer as Pointer and node as Integer returns Boolean
    interleave_memory as Function that takes pointers as List[Pointer] and nodes as List[Integer] returns Boolean
    migrate_memory as Function that takes pointer as Pointer and target_node as Integer returns Boolean
    numa_aware_allocator as Function that takes config as AllocatorConfig and node as Integer returns Allocator
    numa_aware_gc as Function that takes config as GCConfig and node as Integer returns GCAlgorithm
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NUMANode":
    node_id as Integer
    cpus as List[Integer]
    memory as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core NUMA Support Functions
Process called "detect_nodes" that takes numa as NUMASupport returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: Detects NUMA nodes and topology
    Return list of NUMANode

Process called "bind_memory" that takes numa as NUMASupport and pointer as Pointer and node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Binds memory to a specific NUMA node
    Return true

Process called "interleave_memory" that takes numa as NUMASupport and pointers as List[Pointer] and nodes as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Note: Interleaves memory across NUMA nodes
    Return true

Process called "migrate_memory" that takes numa as NUMASupport and pointer as Pointer and target_node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Migrates memory to a target NUMA node
    Return true

Process called "numa_aware_allocator" that takes numa as NUMASupport and config as AllocatorConfig and node as Integer returns Allocator:
    Note: Creates a NUMA-aware allocator
    Return Allocator

Process called "numa_aware_gc" that takes numa as NUMASupport and config as GCConfig and node as Integer returns GCAlgorithm:
    Note: Creates a NUMA-aware GC
    Return GCAlgorithm 